# Append-only memory files: use git's union merge driver to keep all events
# from both sides of a branch merge. Critical for worktree-based multi-agent
# workflows (e.g. squadron pattern: ~/worktrees/<agent>/) where every agent
# accumulates its own events on its own branch and the merge wave folds them
# back into main without conflict.
#
# Without this, every wave merge conflicts on timeline.jsonl because both
# branches added unique lines and git's default text merger can't tell that
# append-only semantics make union safe.
.dejavue/timeline.jsonl merge=union
.dejavue/decisions.md   merge=union
